text:
Astoria Park (Queens): Scenes of the Park on the East River shore. Note, in view 1, a portion of the steel structure of the Triborough Bridge under construction. View 2 shows kids playing on a mound while the park is being improved. View 3 shows an ancient house, one of the remaining few homes from the time when this area was a fashionable residential district, and gas tanks.

P. L. Sperr

View 1: Sept. 20, 1934
View 2: November 9, 1935
View 3: July 10, 1937
title: Queens: Astoria Park.
